						"title": "Get a free PCI DSS 4.0 client-side risk assessment",
						"subtitle": "See if third-party resources are compromising your web visitors",
						"copy": "With the new PCI DSS 4.0 requirements, organizations that process payments have to contend with new controls such as enhanced authentication, encryption, and other security controls. One big change from earlier versions of PCI is the introduction of new client-side security requirements in PCI DSS 4.0.\n\nNew research from Cloudflare<a href=\"https://cfl.re/3KRASrZ\">¹</a> shows that enterprise websites average 47 third-party scripts—a significant attack surface for supply chain compromise.  \n\nOur free PCI DSS 4.0 client-side risk assessment will:\n- Identify malicious activity in third-party scripts compromising your end users' devices and data \n- Help assess your compliance with PCI DSS 4.0 client-side requirements (6.4.3 and 11.6.1)\n- Protect your websites with a positive security model and block all third party components not defined by policy \n\nSign up today to uncover web app supply chain gaps and get your pressing PCI DSS 4.0 questions answered. The assessment requires no hardware or software installation and will not impact website performance or the web experience. \n\n<a href=\"https://cfl.re/3KRASrZ\">¹ State of Application Security 2024 report</a>",
